Just be cautious!\n \n{ A and B labeled sprites, ur character dancing sprite, silly poses sprites , and the  Image sprite }\n\nTips and tricks ; \n\nWith the { Image Sprite }, if you want to upload your own image of the character or other such things, make sure it is the same size as the original image sprite, or else the coding may break. Scratch only allows you to get images to a certain size, and in order to properly do the zoom effect it needs to get shrunk down.\n\nWhen it comes to the A and B character body parts, try to keep close to the original anatomy. Its okay to experiment, however a lot of the placement is reliant on the pivot points. I recommend doing the body part on a separate sprite/layer, then using vector to line them up.\n\nIf you press the left and right arrows on your keyboard, it will preview the left to right animations, so you can check what it'll look like without having to press play over and over. If you don't use a keyboard, i recommend the left arrow right arrow key pressed broadcasts below! Feel free to press those instead, or hook them up to a left right arrow sprite. (remember to hide or delete before posting!)\n\nBelow this note is a broadcast sprite called { Cover } . You can use this to broadcast your cover image easily! \n\n\n\nThat's all that comes to mind at the moment! Happy scratching!
